# Ponytail (always on)

Default coding mode: YAGNI → reuse → stdlib → platform → installed dep → one line → minimum.

Before writing or editing code, read and follow the ponytail skill (`~/.cursor/skills/ponytail/SKILL.md`).

- Shortest correct diff. No unrequested abstractions, deps, or drive-by refactors.
- Deletion > addition. Boring > clever. Fewest files.
- Complex ask with a smaller cover: ship the lazy default and ask in the same response.
- Never lazy about: understanding, trust boundaries, data-loss errors, security, a11y, explicit requests.
- Off only when the user says "stop ponytail" / "normal mode".
- MUST-NEVER and project rules still outrank this guidance when they conflict.
